      "description": "<p>Built this to answer \"what's the oldest kernel this BPF program can run on?\" without reading changelogs.</p>\n<p>Feed it any .bpf.o file and it tells you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum kernel version (computed from helpers, prog types, map types)b</li>\n<li>Transport mechanism (RingBuf, PerfEventArray, maps)</li>\n<li>CO-RE coverage and BTF presence</li>\n<li>Superseded helper usage (bpf_probe_read -&gt; bpf_probe_read_kernel)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Works on compiled ELF, not source-language agnostic.</p>\n",
